  <div class="blog_block">

    <span class="blog_header">Ben Stiller: Owen Wilson&#039;s Pain "Impossible to Understand"</span>

    <br /><span class="blogdatetext">Friday July 18, 2008</span>    <p> 
    <div class="img_container"><div class="blog_img1"><img src="http://www.usmagazine.com/files/wilson-stiller-b.jpg" alt="Ben Stiller and Owen Wilson" title="" width="290" height="463" /></div>Owen Wilson and Ben Stiller at the "Starsky and Hutch" London Premiere on March 11, 2004.<br />Alan Davidson/WireImage.com<div style='clear: both;'></div><div id="buzzbg"><script src="http://d.yimg.com/ds/badge.js" badgetype="small">us_weekly995:http://www.usmagazine.com/node/19038</script></div></div><p><i>Tropic Thunder</i> director and star <b>Ben Stiller</b> has opened up about pal <a href="http://www.usmagazine.com/owen_wilson_myspace_video" target="_blank">Owen Wilson's suicide attempt</a> last August.</p>
<p>"It's impossible to understand that kind of pain – depression or anything like that – until you're in it," Stiller tells <i>Playboy</i> in the August issue of the magazine.</p>
<p>"I love Owen," he says of his <I>Royal Tenenbaums</i> co-star. "I felt bad that he had to deal with all the outside bulls--t."</p>
<p>(<b>Matthew McConaughey</b> replaced Wilson in <i>Tropic Thunder</i>.)</p>
<p>(<a href="http://www.usmagazine.com/Bromances-0708" target="_blank">See photos of other Hollywood Bromances</a>.)</p>
<p>Stiller, 42, also reveals that he was "blown away" by <i>Tropic Thunder</i> co-star <b>Robert Downey Jr.</b></p>
<p>"I started trying to copy him," the comic says. "It was like, 'Wow, this guy's a genius; maybe if I do what he does, I'll be a genius too!'"</p>
<p>Stiller jokes: "If he had spun around and thrown oat bran at the moon, I'd have run out, bought some oat bran and started spinning. I want to look like I'm as big a genius as he is."</p>
<p><b>Tom Cruise</b>'s anticipated role as a studio chief – for which he wore a fat suit – in <i>Tropic Thunder</i> was his own idea, Stiller says.  </p>
<p>"It wasn't even in the script," Stiller says. "I didn't have to persuade him."</p>
<p>The actor tells <i>Playboy</i> that "people would rather dwell on somebody else's problems than look at their own" – and revealed he's just like <i>Us</i>!</p>
<p>"Do I want to pick up a copy of <i>U.S. News &amp; World Report</i> or grab <i>Us Weekly</i>?" he asks. "If I'm in a checkout line, I'll take the one with the big pictures."</p>
<p>So is there a line of humiliation that the jokester won't consider?</p>
<p>"I think I'd draw the line at porn, but no one has asked," Stiller tells <I>Playboy</i>.</p>
<p><i>Tropic Thunder</i> opens August 13.</p>
<p>(<a href="http://www.usmagazine.com/summers-hot-movie-couples" target="_blank">See photos of Summer's Hot Movie Couples</a>.)</p>
<p>Tell <b>Us</b>: Are you looking forward to <i>Tropic Thunder</i>?</p>
