<h3 class="title"></h3>    <div class="comments_time"></div>
		  <span class="comments_time"> 1:13 PM </span>  <span class="comments_subhead">
		  It's Not a Joke Says:		  </span>
		  <br />

    <div class="content"><p>I'm a nurse at a psychological treatment ward in a hospital in Delaware. </p>
<p>IMO - Owen seemed to have experienced what's called "double depression". That's when a person with dysthymia (or a chronic low-grade depression) falls into a major depressive episode. It's quite serious (life-threatening, actually) as the person doesn't have the same resources for dealing with the major depression as a non-depressed person would. First, with this condition, it's much harder to treat than common depression. Also, the effects of the depression are longer-lasting and it leaves the person at a much higher risk for future dehabilitating episodes. In short, if this is indeed his diagnosis, then the man is not well.</p>
<p>That said, I strongly believe that if Owen Wilson chooses not to speak publicly about his condition, then no-one else should either. Other celebs commenting about his medical condition reduces the seriousness of it. It's for him to talk about, or no-one at all.</p>
<p>I hope once Owen finishes with his film commitments, he takes some real time off and receives all the proper treatment he requires. It's not a condition to be taken lightly.</p>
</div>
